## Key Layui DOM patterns I've discovered:

**Layui tables:** Original `<table>` elements become hidden. Layui renders in `.layui-table-view[lay-id=TABLEID]`. Action buttons are inside `.layui-table-view .layui-btn`. Table data rows are in `.layui-table-main tbody tr`.

**Layui selects:** Original `<select>` elements become hidden. Use `page.evaluate()` to set values, or find the Layui-rendered dd items.

**Layui tabs:** Use `.layui-tab-title li:nth-child(N)` to click. Content renders inside `.layui-tab-item` divs. Tables in non-active tabs render with 0 width — must wait for tab to be active before checking table data.

**Layui layer prompts:** `layer.prompt` creates `.layui-layer-prompt` with `.layui-layer-input` and `.layui-layer-btn0` (confirm).

**Layui layer confirms:** `layer.confirm` creates `.layui-layer-btn0` (yes) and `.layui-layer-btn1` (no).

**Layui layer messages:** `layer.msg` creates `.layui-layer-msg`.

## Actual verified DOM state:

**Review page:** The review queue table has rows only when `in_review` recipes exist. The action button is a `.layui-btn-normal` with text "Review" and `lay-event="review"`. Clicking it shows `#review-detail-panel` with `#review-comment-text`, `#btn-add-comment`, `#btn-approve-recipe`, `#btn-reject-recipe`.

**Settlement page:** After clicking Statements tab (2nd tab), the table renders lazily. Each row has a "View" button (`.layui-btn-normal` with `lay-event="view"`). Clicking View shows `#statement-detail-panel` with `#statement-status-badge`, `#btn-submit-statement`, `#btn-approve-statement`, `#btn-reverse-statement`. The generate dialog has `#gen-site-id` (number input) and `#gen-period` (text input).

**Analytics page:** KPI cards are in `#analytics-kpi-row` which starts `display:none`. When data loads, it becomes visible. KPI values populate `#akpi-total-sales` etc. Clicking `.kpi-card[data-metric=X]` opens a `layui.layer` with metric definition text. `#analytics-apply-btn` applies filters. `#analytics-refresh-btn` triggers refresh.

**Recipe editor:** `#btn-new-recipe` → layer.prompt → `#recipe-form-panel` becomes visible. Form has `#recipe-title`, `#recipe-difficulty`, `#recipe-prep-time`, `#recipe-cook-time`, `#recipe-total-time`, `#recipe-tags`, `#recipe-steps-container` with `.step-row` elements, `#recipe-content-editor` (contenteditable), `#recipe-image-upload` (layui.upload, creates hidden file input), `#recipe-image-preview`, `#btn-save-draft`, `#btn-submit-review`.

**Audit page:** Content renders in `#audit-content`. Tabs with `.layui-tab-title li`. Table data loads asynchronously. Filter controls: `#audit-filter-event-type`, `#btn-audit-search`.

